<HEADLINE>
SUPPLIES, TEMPERS SHORT IN GAS-HUNGRY L.A.
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY GREGORY J. WILCOX  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Like a runaway bull market, gasoline prices in the
Los Angeles area continued their rapid rise on Thursday and in some
cases jumped 10 cents from the previous day's level.
</P>
<P>
   The sudden price surge, which saw the cost of a gallon of gas
jump by 25 cents during the past 14 days, could last for at least
two more weeks or possibly a bit longer, analysts and industry
officials predicted.
</P>
<P>
   A gallon of premium gasoline was selling for more than $1.70 a
