<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ LUFKIN, Texas _ A fellow who moved here from
the big city was asking how best to describe our little hometown to
folks who've never been here. Not to brag, but people who have
lived here all their lives and never been anywhere else will tell
you there's no place like Lufkin. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ World War I was started in the
Balkans by a lone gunman. Future generations may tell how World War
III was started in the Balkans by a lone television cameraman.
Television cameras are a greater threat to world peace than nuclear
weapons. (Rowland Nethaway is senior editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   LATHAM-COLUMN _ MARSHALL, Texas _ The moral of this story:
Without the proper amount of gun control, firearms can be extremely
hazardous to your feet. (Latham, Marshall News Messenger) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MINTER-COLUMN _ FAYETTE COUNTY, Ga. _ Against my better
judgment, me and my wife are off to Australia, New Zealand and the
Fiji Islands. I hope our friend Bobby doesn't cause any problems I
can't handle. After he passed the security check at Hartsfield
Airport I'm pretty sure he left his pistol at home, but I don't
know about the bib overalls. If they show up at the Sydney opera
house, so be it. (Jim Minter is a former editor of The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ (McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVES FRIDAY.
