</P>
<P>
   STEPHANOPOULOS-NYTSF, ALL TOO HUMAN: A POLITICAL EDUCATION. By
George Stephanopoulos. Illustrated. 456 pp. Boston: Little, Brown &AMP;
Company. $27.95. The author explains how he escaped the White House
inner circle in tome to avoid corruption.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-NYTSF, UNCOVERING CLINTON: A REPORTER'S STORY by Michael
Isikoff. 402 pp. New York: Crown Publishers. $25. A Newsweek
reporter tells how he got the story of Clinton's sexual misconduct.
</P>
<P>
   FALLING-NYTSF, FALLING: THE STORY OF ONE MARRIAGE. By John
Taylor. Random House. $22.95. The disintegration of a marriage,
from the husband's point of view.
</P>
<P>
   MERWIN-NYTSF, THE RIVER SOUND Poems. By W. S. Merwin. Alfred A.
Knopf. $23. W.S. Merwin contemplates his ancestors and his own
happy, later years.
</P>
