   COXNET NASCAR 0401 _ Its meteoric rise from the backwoods to the
big time has been staggering for NASCAR, now in its 51st stock-car
racing season. NASCAR's growth has been unprecedented in sports,
but for every plus there's a minus, and the sport faces major
issues and decisions that will shape its future. (Schlabach,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (Art includes 3-column color photo of
racing at Atlanta Motor Speedway, 1 column color photo of Bill
France Jr., 2-column color photo of Jeff Gordon eating lunch with
children, 1-column color graphic showing attendance levels at
NASCAR events from 1992 to 1998)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   RISING PRICES BOX -- The NFL has the highest ``Fan Cost Index''
of the spectator sports ranked by Team Marketing Report, Inc. A
look at prices of attending various sports. (Art includes 1-column
color photo of racing.)
</P>
<P>
   WINSTON CUP NOTES -- Most Winston Cup drivers are enjoying a
rare weekend off for Easter, but racing fans still can watch action
in NASCAR's other two series. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) (Art includes color mug of driver Mike
Skinner.)
