<P>
   WINSTON CUP STANDINGS
</P>
<P>
   BUSCH GRAND NATIONAL STANDINGS
</P>
<P>
   NEXT RACE, PREVIOUS WINNERS (Art includes four mugshots of
winners of 1999 Winston Cup events.)
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL-SUIT _ When Sterling Lapinski settled into his seat at
Turner Field on a pleasant summer evening in July 1997, he expected
to watch the Braves and drink some cold beers with his buddies from
work. Then the unthinkable happened. New York Mets catcher Todd
Pratt swung and missed a Tom Glavine fastball. His bat slipped out
of his hands and sailed 100 feet into the stands. Lapinski, who was
looking away, turned back toward the field after hearing warning
shouts from the crowd. Pratt's bat slammed into his forehead. With
blood gushing from his nose and in excruciating pain, he was taken
to Crawford Long Hospital where doctors told him the bat had
shattered his skull, crushed his sinus cavity and tore the lining
of his brain. Lapinski has turned from spectator to plaintiff,
filing a federal lawsuit against the Mets ballclub and its owners,
Sterling Doubleday Enterprises, seeking compensatory damages for
his medical bills and for his pain and suffering. (Rankin, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 42. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (s) Sports and (a) General News categories.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKC-UGA-ADAMS _ University of Georgia president Michael Adams
has taken an active role in the hiring of the school's basketball
coach, conducting interviews with athletics director Vince Dooley,
and his friendship with coach Jim Harrick might have helped him get
the inside track to the job. In fact, it was Adams who was present
at Thursday's press conference when Harrick changed his mind and
decided to stay at Georgia. Unlike former UGA president Charles
Knapp, Adams is taking a highly-visible role in the athletic
department. (Brice, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-UGA-HARRICK _ Jim Harrick has returned to Athens and is
expected to have his first official meeting with the Georgia
players this afternoon. What type of reception will Harrick receive
after changing his mind back and forth over the last two days?
(Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
