<P>
   STUCCO _ The residential market for synthetic stucco washed out
like a broken dam two years ago, after complaints about moisture
intrusion were splashed all over the news. Before you could say
``plug the hole,'' a spate of alternative products began filling it
up. Meanwhile, competitors such Hebel and Ytong, Elite Cement and
Sider-Oxydro have been trying hard to tell metro Atlanta builders
that there are other ways to have the stucco look and insulation
attributes. (Harte, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
