   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SPACE-STATION (Houston) _ The United States will offer Russia
another $100 million in an attempt to keep the international space
station project on schedule. Ostensibly, the money will purchase a
three-person Soyuz capsule and other gear. But the real objective,
according to NASA administrator Dan Goldin, is to keep the more
crucial Russian contributions to the new station from slipping
further behind schedule. By MARK CARREAU. (Filed Friday.)
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``i'' category)
</P>
<P>
   ECUADOR-SLAYING (Quito, Ecuador) _ Unlike neighboring Colombia
and Peru, Ecuador has never been plagued by death squads, powerful
guerrilla armies or drug-cartel terrorism. Thus, the murder of
Jaime Hurtado, a Marxist congressman, has left Ecuadoreans baffled.
The government blames Colombian paramilitaries. Others suspect the
police. Regardless, the slaying has shattered the illusion of
Ecuador as a safe haven from regional violence. By JOHN OTIS.
(Filed Friday.)
