column on Mark McGwire and Sammy Sosa as they prepare for their
encore to last season's magic. With graphic and photo. By Dave
Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-SEASON-JETER (Undated) _ Ask around Kalamazoo, Mich., and
everybody seems to have only good things to say about Derek Jeter
and his family. Derek was the type of kid, Evelyn Lal said, ``that
you wanted your kid to be friends with.'' Shanti Lal, her son,
befriended Derek in the fourth grade, in Mrs. Garzelloni's class at
St. Augustine Cathedral School in Kalamazoo. ``Derek was one of
those kids you just never forget, and I would say that even if he
wasn't playing baseball,'' said Shirley Garzelloni, who retired
last year. Buster Olney visits the hometown of Derek Jeter, the
Yankees' shortstop and rising superstar.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-SEASON-PIAZZA (Port St. Lucie, Fla.) _ As he prepares to
enter his first full season as the centerpiece of a rebuilt New
York Mets offense, and claim his place on the most demanding of
sports stages, Mike Piazza remains an enigmatic superstar. By Jason
Diamos.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-SEASON-PREDICTIONS (Undated) _ New York Times sportswriters
Murray Chass, Jack Curry, Buster Olney and Jason Diamos offer their
predictions for the 1999 season, including their projected World
Series champions.
