   KOSOVO-MILITARY (Washington) _ Ledeall: NATO forces struck
targets in the center of the Yugoslav capital Belgrade on Friday
night for the first time since the Kosovo campaign began on March
24. Shortly afterward, Yugoslav televsion began showing pictures of
the Interior Ministry building engulfed in flames. By Steven Lee
Myers.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-BELGRADE (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ The scene as the
capital comes under attack. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-REFUGEES (Morini, Albania) _ With ethnic Albanian
refugees from Kosovo continuing to stream across the tiny mountain
border crossing here at the rate of more than 2,000 an hour,
officials said today the week-old exodus is creating an ominous
humanitarian crisis. ``The situation is out of control. It is
catastrophic,'' the Albanian information minister, Musa Ulqini,
