<P>
   MUTFUND-VALUE (Undated) _ Value managers have long shunned what
they view as overvalued growth stocks. Instead, they favor stocks
with lower price-to-earnings or other valuation ratios. But that
has lately brought grief for their shareholders, as stocks
relatively cheap by traditional measures continue to be clobbered
by the big growth companies. By Richard A. Oppel Jr. WITH GRAPHICS
and PHOTO.
