 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-FLA-TEEN-SMOKING-NYT (moved on Thursday, Apr. 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Apr. 1,
about the decrease in smoking by Florida students in the sixth to
eighth grades misstated last year's decline in some copies. It was
19 percent, not 19 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MURDOCH-MALONE-NYT (moved on Thursday, Apr. 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Apr. 1,
about Rupert Murdoch's plan to buy the 50 percent stake owned by
Liberty Media in their joint sports venture misstated the status of
his purchase of the British soccer team Manchester United. Mr.
Murdoch's satellite company, BSkyB, has bid for the team. It does
not own it.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-COUPONS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Mar. 31)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Mar.
31, about on-line coupons used an obsolete name for a company that
offers E-centives, redeemable on line. While it used to be called
Emaginet, its name is now E-centives Inc.
</P>
